#Text=The New York Knicks ( 19 - 20 ) beat the Milwaukee Bucks ( 15 - 24 ) 100 - 88 on Sunday night .
#Text=Most people would have expected the Bucks to be the better team at this point of the year , but this result shows just where these two teams are at right now .
#Text=Milwaukee is one of the worst road teams in the NBA , as they are now 5 - 17 away from BMO Harris Bradley Center .
#Text=What killed them here were the second and third quarters , in which they were outscored 58 - 36 .
#Text=The benches were also a huge difference , as Milwaukee got just 14 points off their bench to the Knicks 28 .
#Text=The Bucks continue to play bad basketball and it 's a bit concerning with their starters playing so many minutes .
#Text=Greg Monroe had been struggling lately , but he played well here , as he totaled 28 points and 10 rebounds in the loss .
#Text=Khris Middleton also continued his scoring ways , as he scored 20 points , but failed to stuff the stat sheet like he usually does .
#Text=What really hurt was a 1 - for - 8 shooting performance from Michael Carter-Williams , who was playing some of his best ball of the season prior to this game .
#Text=The Bucks will look to bounce - back on Tuesday against the Chicago Bulls in their next game .
#Text=The Knicks have been one of the surprises of the NBA this season and the all - around play of Carmelo Anthony is the most surprising aspect .
#Text=Anthony is approaching a career - high in assists this season and is handling the offense better than he ever has in his career .
#Text=In this game , he collected 24 points , 10 rebounds and eight assists in the win .
#Text=Kristaps Porzingis continued his good play too , as he scored 15 points and swatted away five shots .
#Text=The five starters combined for 22 assists and that 's a great number for any team .
#Text=New York will look to keep this going against the Boston Celtics on Tuesday .
